quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  7,105,worthy to say nothing regarding God except the truth. I have brought a clear sign to you from your Lord; so send forth with me the Children of Israel
  7,106,"Said he, 'If thou hast brought a sign, produce it, if thou speakest truly"
  7,107,"So he cast his staff; and behold, it was a serpent manifest"
  7,108,"And he drew forth his hand, and lo, it was white to the beholders"
  7,109,"Said the Council of the people of Pharaoh, 'Surely this man is a cunning sorcerer"
  7,110,who desires to expel you from your land; what do you command
  7,111,"They said, 'Put him and his brother off a while, and send among the cities musterers"
  7,112,to bring thee every cunning sorcerer
  7,113,"And the sorcerers came to Pharaoh, saying, 'We shall surely have a wage, if we should be the victors"
  7,114,"He said, 'Yes, indeed; and you shall be among the near-stationed"
  7,115,"They said, 'Moses, wilt thou cast, or shall we be the casters"
  7,116,"He said, 'You cast.' And when they cast they put a Spell upon the people's eyes, and called forth fear of them, and produced a mighty sorcery"
  7,117,"And We revealed to Moses: 'Cast thy staff!' And lo, it forthwith swallowed up their lying invention"
  7,118,"So the truth came to pass, and false was proved what they were doing"
  7,119,"So they were vanquished there, and they turned about, humbled"
  7,120,"And the sorcerers were cast down, bowing themselves"